  "text": "Pose estimation is a well-studied problem in computer vision. Initially, research on the topic focused primarily on instance-level pose estimation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In instancelevel pose estimation, the model is trained on each specific object instance. Given enough training images of a single instance, the problem essentially reduces to constructing a 3D model of the instance and then finding the pose of the 3D model that best matches the test instance.",
